{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Well this is a really extraordinary honor for me."},{"time":3000,"text":"I spend most of my time"},{"time":5000,"text":"in jails, in prisons, on death row."},{"time":8000,"text":"I spend most of my time in very low-income communities"},{"time":11000,"text":"in the projects and places where there's a great deal of hopelessness."},{"time":14000,"text":"And being here at TED"},{"time":16000,"text":"and seeing the stimulation, hearing it,"},{"time":18000,"text":"has been very, very energizing to me."},{"time":20000,"text":"And one of the things that's emerged in my short time here"},{"time":23000,"text":"is that TED has an identity."},{"time":26000,"text":"And you can actually say things here"},{"time":28000,"text":"that have impacts around the world."},{"time":30000,"text":"And sometimes when it comes through TED,"},{"time":32000,"text":"it has meaning and power"},{"time":34000,"text":"that it doesn't have when it doesn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"And I mention that because I think identity is really important."},{"time":40000,"text":"And we've had some fantastic presentations."},{"time":43000,"text":"And I think what we've learned"},{"time":45000,"text":"is that, if you're a teacher your words can be meaningful,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but if you're a compassionate teacher,"},{"time":49000,"text":"they can be especially meaningful."},{"time":51000,"text":"If you're a doctor you can do some good things,"},{"time":53000,"text":"but if you're a caring doctor you can do some other things."},{"time":56000,"text":"And so I want to talk about the power of identity."},{"time":59000,"text":"And I didn't learn about this actually"},{"time":61000,"text":"practicing law and doing the work that I do."},{"time":63000,"text":"I actually learned about this from my grandmother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"I grew up in a house"},{"time":68000,"text":"that was the traditional African-American home"},{"time":70000,"text":"that was dominated by a matriarch,"},{"time":72000,"text":"and that matriarch was my grandmother."},{"time":74000,"text":"She was tough, she was strong,"},{"time":77000,"text":"she was powerful."},{"time":79000,"text":"She was the end of every argument in our family."},{"time":83000,"text":"She was the beginning of a lot of arguments in our family."},{"time":86000,"text":"She was the daughter of people who were actually enslaved."},{"time":89000,"text":"Her parents were born in slavery in Virginia in the 1840's."},{"time":91000,"text":"She was born in the 1880's"},{"time":93000,"text":"and the experience of slavery"},{"time":95000,"text":"very much shaped the way she saw the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"And my grandmother was tough, but she was also loving."},{"time":100000,"text":"When I would see her as a little boy,"},{"time":102000,"text":"she'd come up to me and she'd give me these hugs."},{"time":104000,"text":"And she'd squeeze me so tight I could barely breathe"},{"time":106000,"text":"and then she'd let me go."},{"time":108000,"text":"And an hour or two later, if I saw her,"},{"time":110000,"text":"she'd come over to me and she'd say, \"Bryan, do you still feel me hugging you?\""},{"time":113000,"text":"And if I said, \"No,\" she'd assault me again,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and if I said, \"Yes,\" she'd leave me alone."},{"time":117000,"text":"And she just had this quality"},{"time":119000,"text":"that you always wanted to be near her."},{"time":121000,"text":"And the only challenge was that she had 10 children."},{"time":124000,"text":"My mom was the youngest of her 10 kids."},{"time":126000,"text":"And sometimes when I would go and spend time with her,"},{"time":128000,"text":"it would be difficult to get her time and attention."},{"time":130000,"text":"My cousins would be running around everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"And I remember, when I was about eight or nine years old,"},{"time":135000,"text":"waking up one morning, going into the living room,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and all of my cousins were running around."},{"time":139000,"text":"And my grandmother was sitting across the room"},{"time":141000,"text":"staring at me."},{"time":143000,"text":"And at first I thought we were playing a game."},{"time":145000,"text":"And I would look at her and I'd smile,"},{"time":147000,"text":"but she was very serious."},{"time":149000,"text":"And after about 15 or 20 minutes of this,"},{"time":151000,"text":"she got up and she came across the room"},{"time":154000,"text":"and she took me by the hand"},{"time":156000,"text":"and she said, \"Come on, Bryan. You and I are going to have a talk.\""},{"time":158000,"text":"And I remember this just like it happened yesterday."},{"time":162000,"text":"I never will forget it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"She took me out back and she said, \"Bryan, I'm going to tell you something,"},{"time":166000,"text":"but you don't tell anybody what I tell you.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"I said, \"Okay, Mama.\""},{"time":170000,"text":"She said, \"Now you make sure you don't do that.\" I said, \"Sure.\""},{"time":173000,"text":"Then she sat me down and she looked at me"},{"time":176000,"text":"and she said, \"I want you to know"},{"time":178000,"text":"I've been watching you.\""},{"time":181000,"text":"And she said, \"I think you're special.\""},{"time":184000,"text":"She said, \"I think you can do anything you want to do.\""},{"time":188000,"text":"I will never forget it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"And then she said, \"I just need you to promise me three things, Bryan.\""},{"time":193000,"text":"I said, \"Okay, Mama.\""},{"time":195000,"text":"She said, \"The first thing I want you to promise me"},{"time":197000,"text":"is that you'll always love your mom.\""},{"time":199000,"text":"She said, \"That's my baby girl,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and you have to promise me now you'll always take care of her.\""},{"time":203000,"text":"Well I adored my mom, so I said, \"Yes, Mama. I'll do that.\""},{"time":207000,"text":"Then she said, \"The second thing I want you to promise me"},{"time":209000,"text":"is that you'll always do the right thing"},{"time":211000,"text":"even when the right thing is the hard thing.\""},{"time":214000,"text":"And I thought about it and I said, \"Yes, Mama. I'll do that.\""},{"time":218000,"text":"Then finally she said, \"The third thing I want you to promise me"},{"time":220000,"text":"is that you'll never drink alcohol.\""},{"time":223000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":225000,"text":"Well I was nine years old, so I said, \"Yes, Mama. I'll do that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"I grew up in the country in the rural South,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and I have a brother a year older than me and a sister a year younger."},{"time":233000,"text":"When I was about 14 or 15,"},{"time":235000,"text":"one day my brother came home and he had this six-pack of beer --"},{"time":237000,"text":"I don't know where he got it --"},{"time":239000,"text":"and he grabbed me and my sister and we went out in the woods."},{"time":241000,"text":"And we were kind of just out there doing the stuff we crazily did."},{"time":244000,"text":"And he had a sip of this beer and he gave some to my sister and she had some,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and they offered it to me."},{"time":249000,"text":"I said, \"No, no, no. That's okay. You all go ahead. I'm not going to have any beer.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"My brother said, \"Come on. We're doing this today; you always do what we do."},{"time":255000,"text":"I had some, your sister had some. Have some beer.\""},{"time":257000,"text":"I said, \"No, I don't feel right about that. Y'all go ahead. Y'all go ahead.\""},{"time":259000,"text":"And then my brother started staring at me."},{"time":261000,"text":"He said, \"What's wrong with you? Have some beer.\""},{"time":264000,"text":"Then he looked at me real hard and he said,"},{"time":266000,"text":"\"Oh, I hope you're not still hung up"},{"time":268000,"text":"on that conversation Mama had with you.\""},{"time":270000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":272000,"text":"I said, \"Well, what are you talking about?\""},{"time":274000,"text":"He said, \"Oh, Mama tells all the grandkids that they're special.\""},{"time":277000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":280000,"text":"I was devastated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"And I'm going to admit something to you."},{"time":286000,"text":"I'm going to tell you something I probably shouldn't."},{"time":288000,"text":"I know this might be broadcast broadly."},{"time":290000,"text":"But I'm 52 years old,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and I'm going to admit to you"},{"time":294000,"text":"that I've never had a drop of alcohol."},{"time":297000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":299000,"text":"I don't say that because I think that's virtuous;"},{"time":302000,"text":"I say that because there is power in identity."},{"time":306000,"text":"When we create the right kind of identity,"},{"time":308000,"text":"we can say things to the world around us"},{"time":310000,"text":"that they don't actually believe makes sense."},{"time":312000,"text":"We can get them to do things"},{"time":314000,"text":"that they don't think they can do."},{"time":316000,"text":"When I thought about my grandmother,"},{"time":318000,"text":"of course she would think all her grandkids were special."},{"time":320000,"text":"My grandfather was in prison during prohibition."},{"time":323000,"text":"My male uncles died of alcohol-related diseases."},{"time":325000,"text":"And these were the things she thought we needed to commit to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"Well I've been trying to say something"},{"time":330000,"text":"about our criminal justice system."},{"time":332000,"text":"This country is very different today"},{"time":334000,"text":"than it was 40 years ago."},{"time":336000,"text":"In 1972, there were 300,000 people in jails and prisons."},{"time":339000,"text":"Today, there are 2.3 million."},{"time":344000,"text":"The United States now has the highest rate of incarceration"},{"time":346000,"text":"in the world."},{"time":348000,"text":"We have seven million people on probation and parole."},{"time":351000,"text":"And mass incarceration, in my judgment,"},{"time":354000,"text":"has fundamentally changed our world."},{"time":357000,"text":"In poor communities, in communities of color"},{"time":359000,"text":"there is this despair,"},{"time":361000,"text":"there is this hopelessness,"},{"time":363000,"text":"that is being shaped by these outcomes."},{"time":365000,"text":"One out of three black men"},{"time":367000,"text":"between the ages of 18 and 30"},{"time":369000,"text":"is in jail, in prison, on probation or parole."},{"time":372000,"text":"In urban communities across this country --"},{"time":374000,"text":"Los Angeles, Philadelphia, Baltimore, Washington --"},{"time":377000,"text":"50 to 60 percent of all young men of color are"},{"time":380000,"text":"in jail or prison or on probation or parole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"Our system isn't just being shaped"},{"time":385000,"text":"in these ways that seem to be distorting around race,"},{"time":387000,"text":"they're also distorted by poverty."},{"time":389000,"text":"We have a system of justice in this country"},{"time":392000,"text":"that treats you much better"},{"time":394000,"text":"if you're rich and guilty than if you're poor and innocent."},{"time":397000,"text":"Wealth, not culpability,"},{"time":400000,"text":"shapes outcomes."},{"time":402000,"text":"And yet, we seem to be very comfortable."},{"time":405000,"text":"The politics of fear and anger"},{"time":407000,"text":"have made us believe"},{"time":409000,"text":"that these are problems that are not our problems."},{"time":412000,"text":"We've been disconnected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"It's interesting to me."},{"time":416000,"text":"We're looking at some very interesting developments in our work."},{"time":418000,"text":"My state of Alabama, like a number of states,"},{"time":420000,"text":"actually permanently disenfranchises you"},{"time":422000,"text":"if you have a criminal conviction."},{"time":424000,"text":"Right now in Alabama"},{"time":426000,"text":"34 percent of the black male population"},{"time":428000,"text":"has permanently lost the right to vote."},{"time":430000,"text":"We're actually projecting in another 10 years"},{"time":432000,"text":"the level of disenfranchisement"},{"time":434000,"text":"will be as high as it's been"},{"time":436000,"text":"since prior to the passage of the Voting Rights Act."},{"time":438000,"text":"And there is this stunning silence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"I represent children."},{"time":444000,"text":"A lot of my clients are very young."},{"time":446000,"text":"The United States is the only country in the world"},{"time":448000,"text":"where we sentence 13-year-old children"},{"time":450000,"text":"to die in prison."},{"time":452000,"text":"We have life imprisonment without parole for kids in this country."},{"time":455000,"text":"And we're actually doing some litigation."},{"time":457000,"text":"The only country in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"I represent people on death row."},{"time":461000,"text":"It's interesting, this question of the death penalty."},{"time":463000,"text":"In many ways, we've been taught to think"},{"time":465000,"text":"that the real question is,"},{"time":467000,"text":"do people deserve to die for the crimes they've committed?"},{"time":470000,"text":"And that's a very sensible question."},{"time":472000,"text":"But there's another way of thinking"},{"time":474000,"text":"about where we are in our identity."},{"time":476000,"text":"The other way of thinking about it"},{"time":478000,"text":"is not, do people deserve to die for the crimes they commit,"},{"time":480000,"text":"but do we deserve to kill?"},{"time":482000,"text":"I mean, it's fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Death penalty in America is defined by error."},{"time":487000,"text":"For every nine people who have been executed,"},{"time":489000,"text":"we've actually identified one innocent person"},{"time":491000,"text":"who's been exonerated and released from death row."},{"time":494000,"text":"A kind of astonishing error rate --"},{"time":497000,"text":"one out of nine people innocent."},{"time":500000,"text":"I mean, it's fascinating."},{"time":502000,"text":"In aviation, we would never let people fly on airplanes"},{"time":505000,"text":"if for every nine planes that took off"},{"time":507000,"text":"one would crash."},{"time":509000,"text":"But somehow we can insulate ourselves from this problem."},{"time":512000,"text":"It's not our problem."},{"time":514000,"text":"It's not our burden."},{"time":516000,"text":"It's not our struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"I talk a lot about these issues."},{"time":520000,"text":"I talk about race and this question"},{"time":522000,"text":"of whether we deserve to kill."},{"time":524000,"text":"And it's interesting, when I teach my students about African-American history,"},{"time":526000,"text":"I tell them about slavery."},{"time":528000,"text":"I tell them about terrorism,"},{"time":530000,"text":"the era that began at the end of reconstruction"},{"time":532000,"text":"that went on to World War II."},{"time":534000,"text":"We don't really know very much about it."},{"time":536000,"text":"But for African-Americans in this country,"},{"time":538000,"text":"that was an era defined by terror."},{"time":540000,"text":"In many communities, people had to worry about being lynched."},{"time":542000,"text":"They had to worry about being bombed."},{"time":544000,"text":"It was the threat of terror that shaped their lives."},{"time":546000,"text":"And these older people come up to me now"},{"time":548000,"text":"and they say, \"Mr. Stevenson, you give talks, you make speeches,"},{"time":551000,"text":"you tell people to stop saying"},{"time":553000,"text":"we're dealing with terrorism for the first time in our nation's history"},{"time":556000,"text":"after 9/11.\""},{"time":558000,"text":"They tell me to say, \"No, tell them that we grew up with that.\""},{"time":561000,"text":"And that era of terrorism, of course,"},{"time":563000,"text":"was followed by segregation"},{"time":565000,"text":"and decades of racial subordination"},{"time":567000,"text":"and apartheid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569000,"text":"And yet, we have in this country this dynamic"},{"time":572000,"text":"where we really don't like to talk about our problems."},{"time":575000,"text":"We don't like to talk about our history."},{"time":578000,"text":"And because of that, we really haven't understood"},{"time":581000,"text":"what it's meant to do the things we've done historically."},{"time":584000,"text":"We're constantly running into each other."},{"time":586000,"text":"We're constantly creating tensions and conflicts."},{"time":588000,"text":"We have a hard time talking about race,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and I believe it's because we are unwilling to commit ourselves"},{"time":595000,"text":"to a process of truth and reconciliation."},{"time":597000,"text":"In South Africa, people understood"},{"time":599000,"text":"that we couldn't overcome apartheid"},{"time":601000,"text":"without a commitment to truth and reconciliation."},{"time":603000,"text":"In Rwanda, even after the genocide, there was this commitment,"},{"time":606000,"text":"but in this country we haven't done that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"I was giving some lectures in Germany about the death penalty."},{"time":611000,"text":"It was fascinating"},{"time":613000,"text":"because one of the scholars stood up after the presentation"},{"time":616000,"text":"and said, \"Well you know it's deeply troubling"},{"time":618000,"text":"to hear what you're talking about.\""},{"time":620000,"text":"He said, \"We don't have the death penalty in Germany."},{"time":623000,"text":"And of course, we can never have the death penalty in Germany.\""},{"time":626000,"text":"And the room got very quiet,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and this woman said,"},{"time":630000,"text":"\"There's no way, with our history,"},{"time":633000,"text":"we could ever engage"},{"time":635000,"text":"in the systematic killing of human beings."},{"time":637000,"text":"It would be unconscionable for us"},{"time":641000,"text":"to, in an intentional and deliberate way,"},{"time":643000,"text":"set about executing people.\""},{"time":646000,"text":"And I thought about that."},{"time":648000,"text":"What would it feel like"},{"time":650000,"text":"to be living in a world"},{"time":652000,"text":"where the nation state of Germany was executing people,"},{"time":655000,"text":"especially if they were disproportionately Jewish?"},{"time":657000,"text":"I couldn't bear it."},{"time":659000,"text":"It would be unconscionable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"And yet, in this country,"},{"time":663000,"text":"in the states of the Old South,"},{"time":665000,"text":"we execute people --"},{"time":667000,"text":"where you're 11 times more likely to get the death penalty"},{"time":669000,"text":"if the victim is white than if the victim is black,"},{"time":671000,"text":"22 times more likely to get it"},{"time":673000,"text":"if the defendant is black and the victim is white --"},{"time":675000,"text":"in the very states where there are buried in the ground"},{"time":677000,"text":"the bodies of people who were lynched."},{"time":679000,"text":"And yet, there is this disconnect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"Well I believe that our identity is at risk."},{"time":687000,"text":"That when we actually don't care"},{"time":690000,"text":"about these difficult things,"},{"time":693000,"text":"the positive and wonderful things"},{"time":695000,"text":"are nonetheless implicated."},{"time":698000,"text":"We love innovation."},{"time":700000,"text":"We love technology. We love creativity."},{"time":703000,"text":"We love entertainment."},{"time":705000,"text":"But ultimately,"},{"time":707000,"text":"those realities"},{"time":709000,"text":"are shadowed by suffering,"},{"time":712000,"text":"abuse, degradation,"},{"time":714000,"text":"marginalization."},{"time":716000,"text":"And for me, it becomes necessary"},{"time":718000,"text":"to integrate the two."},{"time":720000,"text":"Because ultimately we are talking"},{"time":722000,"text":"about a need to be more hopeful,"},{"time":724000,"text":"more committed, more dedicated"},{"time":727000,"text":"to the basic challenges of living in a complex world."},{"time":730000,"text":"And for me that means"},{"time":733000,"text":"spending time thinking and talking"},{"time":735000,"text":"about the poor, the disadvantaged,"},{"time":738000,"text":"those who will never get to TED."},{"time":740000,"text":"But thinking about them in a way"},{"time":742000,"text":"that is integrated in our own lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"You know ultimately, we all have to believe things we haven't seen."},{"time":748000,"text":"We do. As rational as we are, as committed to intellect as we are."},{"time":752000,"text":"Innovation, creativity,"},{"time":754000,"text":"development comes"},{"time":756000,"text":"not from the ideas in our mind alone."},{"time":758000,"text":"They come from the ideas in our mind"},{"time":761000,"text":"that are also fueled"},{"time":763000,"text":"by some conviction in our heart."},{"time":765000,"text":"And it's that mind-heart connection"},{"time":767000,"text":"that I believe compels us"},{"time":769000,"text":"to not just be attentive"},{"time":771000,"text":"to all the bright and dazzly things,"},{"time":774000,"text":"but also the dark and difficult things."},{"time":777000,"text":"Vaclav Havel, the great Czech leader, talked about this."},{"time":780000,"text":"He said, \"When we were in Eastern Europe and dealing with oppression,"},{"time":783000,"text":"we wanted all kinds of things,"},{"time":785000,"text":"but mostly what we needed was hope,"},{"time":787000,"text":"an orientation of the spirit,"},{"time":789000,"text":"a willingness to sometimes be in hopeless places"},{"time":791000,"text":"and be a witness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"Well that orientation of the spirit"},{"time":795000,"text":"is very much at the core of what I believe"},{"time":798000,"text":"even TED communities"},{"time":800000,"text":"have to be engaged in."},{"time":802000,"text":"There is no disconnect"},{"time":804000,"text":"around technology and design"},{"time":807000,"text":"that will allow us to be fully human"},{"time":809000,"text":"until we pay attention to suffering,"},{"time":812000,"text":"to poverty, to exclusion, to unfairness, to injustice."},{"time":815000,"text":"Now I will warn you"},{"time":817000,"text":"that this kind of identity"},{"time":819000,"text":"is a much more challenging identity"},{"time":822000,"text":"than ones that don't pay attention to this."},{"time":824000,"text":"It will get to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826000,"text":"I had the great privilege, when I was a young lawyer, of meeting Rosa Parks."},{"time":829000,"text":"And Ms. Parks used to come back to Montgomery every now and then,"},{"time":832000,"text":"and she would get together with two of her dearest friends,"},{"time":834000,"text":"these older women,"},{"time":836000,"text":"Johnnie Carr who was the organizer"},{"time":838000,"text":"of the Montgomery bus boycott --"},{"time":840000,"text":"amazing African-American woman --"},{"time":842000,"text":"and Virginia Durr, a white woman,"},{"time":844000,"text":"whose husband, Clifford Durr, represented Dr. King."},{"time":846000,"text":"And these women would get together and just talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"And every now and then Ms. Carr would call me,"},{"time":851000,"text":"and she'd say, \"Bryan, Ms. Parks is coming to town. We're going to get together and talk."},{"time":854000,"text":"Do you want to come over and listen?\""},{"time":856000,"text":"And I'd say, \"Yes, Ma'am, I do.\""},{"time":858000,"text":"And she'd say, \"Well what are you going to do when you get here?\""},{"time":860000,"text":"I said, \"I'm going to listen.\""},{"time":862000,"text":"And I'd go over there and I would, I would just listen."},{"time":864000,"text":"It would be so energizing and so empowering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"And one time I was over there listening to these women talk,"},{"time":869000,"text":"and after a couple of hours Ms. Parks turned to me"},{"time":871000,"text":"and she said, \"Now Bryan, tell me what the Equal Justice Initiative is."},{"time":874000,"text":"Tell me what you're trying to do.\""},{"time":876000,"text":"And I began giving her my rap."},{"time":878000,"text":"I said, \"Well we're trying to challenge injustice."},{"time":880000,"text":"We're trying to help people who have been wrongly convicted."},{"time":882000,"text":"We're trying to confront bias and discrimination"},{"time":884000,"text":"in the administration of criminal justice."},{"time":886000,"text":"We're trying to end life without parole sentences for children."},{"time":889000,"text":"We're trying to do something about the death penalty."},{"time":891000,"text":"We're trying to reduce the prison population."},{"time":893000,"text":"We're trying to end mass incarceration.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"I gave her my whole rap, and when I finished she looked at me"},{"time":897000,"text":"and she said, \"Mmm mmm mmm.\""},{"time":900000,"text":"She said, \"That's going to make you tired, tired, tired.\""},{"time":903000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":905000,"text":"And that's when Ms. Carr leaned forward, she put her finger in my face,"},{"time":907000,"text":"she said, \"That's why you've got to be brave, brave, brave.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"And I actually believe that the TED community"},{"time":916000,"text":"needs to be more courageous."},{"time":918000,"text":"We need to find ways"},{"time":920000,"text":"to embrace these challenges,"},{"time":922000,"text":"these problems, the suffering."},{"time":924000,"text":"Because ultimately, our humanity depends"},{"time":927000,"text":"on everyone's humanity."},{"time":929000,"text":"I've learned very simple things doing the work that I do."},{"time":931000,"text":"It's just taught me very simple things."},{"time":933000,"text":"I've come to understand and to believe"},{"time":936000,"text":"that each of us"},{"time":938000,"text":"is more than the worst thing we've ever done."},{"time":940000,"text":"I believe that for every person on the planet."},{"time":943000,"text":"I think if somebody tells a lie, they're not just a liar."},{"time":946000,"text":"I think if somebody takes something that doesn't belong to them,"},{"time":948000,"text":"they're not just a thief."},{"time":950000,"text":"I think even if you kill someone, you're not just a killer."},{"time":953000,"text":"And because of that there's this basic human dignity"},{"time":956000,"text":"that must be respected by law."},{"time":958000,"text":"I also believe"},{"time":960000,"text":"that in many parts of this country,"},{"time":962000,"text":"and certainly in many parts of this globe,"},{"time":966000,"text":"that the opposite of poverty is not wealth."},{"time":968000,"text":"I don't believe that."},{"time":970000,"text":"I actually think, in too many places,"},{"time":973000,"text":"the opposite of poverty is justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"And finally, I believe"},{"time":979000,"text":"that, despite the fact that it is so dramatic"},{"time":982000,"text":"and so beautiful and so inspiring"},{"time":984000,"text":"and so stimulating,"},{"time":986000,"text":"we will ultimately not be judged by our technology,"},{"time":989000,"text":"we won't be judged by our design,"},{"time":992000,"text":"we won't be judged by our intellect and reason."},{"time":995000,"text":"Ultimately, you judge the character of a society,"},{"time":998000,"text":"not by how they treat their rich and the powerful and the privileged,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"but by how they treat the poor,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"the condemned, the incarcerated."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Because it's in that nexus"},{"time":1007000,"text":"that we actually begin to understand truly profound things"},{"time":1010000,"text":"about who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014000,"text":"I sometimes get out of balance. I'll end with this story."},{"time":1016000,"text":"I sometimes push too hard."},{"time":1018000,"text":"I do get tired, as we all do."},{"time":1020000,"text":"Sometimes those ideas get ahead of our thinking"},{"time":1023000,"text":"in ways that are important."},{"time":1025000,"text":"And I've been representing these kids"},{"time":1027000,"text":"who have been sentenced to do these very harsh sentences."},{"time":1029000,"text":"And I go to the jail and I see my client who's 13 and 14,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and he's been certified to stand trial as an adult."},{"time":1035000,"text":"I start thinking, well, how did that happen?"},{"time":1037000,"text":"How can a judge turn you into something"},{"time":1039000,"text":"that you're not?"},{"time":1041000,"text":"And the judge has certified him as an adult, but I see this kid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"And I was up too late one night and I starting thinking,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"well gosh, if the judge can turn you into something that you're not,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"the judge must have magic power."},{"time":1050000,"text":"Yeah, Bryan, the judge has some magic power."},{"time":1053000,"text":"You should ask for some of that."},{"time":1055000,"text":"And because I was up too late, wasn't thinking real straight,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"I started working on a motion."},{"time":1059000,"text":"And I had a client who was 14 years old, a young, poor black kid."},{"time":1062000,"text":"And I started working on this motion,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"and the head of the motion was: \"Motion to try my poor,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"14-year-old black male client"},{"time":1068000,"text":"like a privileged, white 75-year-old"},{"time":1070000,"text":"corporate executive.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"And I put in my motion"},{"time":1079000,"text":"that there was prosecutorial misconduct and police misconduct and judicial misconduct."},{"time":1082000,"text":"There was a crazy line in there about how there's no conduct in this county,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"it's all misconduct."},{"time":1086000,"text":"And the next morning, I woke up and I thought, now did I dream that crazy motion,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"or did I actually write it?"},{"time":1091000,"text":"And to my horror, not only had I written it,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"but I had sent it to court."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1098000,"text":"A couple months went by,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"and I had just forgotten all about it."},{"time":1103000,"text":"And I finally decided,"},{"time":1105000,"text":"oh gosh, I've got to go to the court and do this crazy case."},{"time":1107000,"text":"And I got into my car"},{"time":1109000,"text":"and I was feeling really overwhelmed -- overwhelmed."},{"time":1111000,"text":"And I got in my car and I went to this courthouse."},{"time":1113000,"text":"And I was thinking, this is going to be so difficult, so painful."},{"time":1116000,"text":"And I finally got out of the car and I started walking up to the courthouse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119000,"text":"And as I was walking up the steps of this courthouse,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"there was an older black man who was the janitor in this courthouse."},{"time":1124000,"text":"When this man saw me, he came over to me"},{"time":1126000,"text":"and he said, \"Who are you?\""},{"time":1128000,"text":"I said, \"I'm a lawyer.\" He said, \"You're a lawyer?\" I said, \"Yes, sir.\""},{"time":1131000,"text":"And this man came over to me"},{"time":1133000,"text":"and he hugged me."},{"time":1135000,"text":"And he whispered in my ear."},{"time":1137000,"text":"He said, \"I'm so proud of you.\""},{"time":1139000,"text":"And I have to tell you,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"it was energizing."},{"time":1143000,"text":"It connected deeply with something in me"},{"time":1145000,"text":"about identity,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"about the capacity of every person to contribute"},{"time":1150000,"text":"to a community, to a perspective that is hopeful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152000,"text":"Well I went into the courtroom."},{"time":1154000,"text":"And as soon as I walked inside, the judge saw me coming in."},{"time":1156000,"text":"He said, \"Mr. Stevenson, did you write this crazy motion?\""},{"time":1159000,"text":"I said, \"Yes, sir. I did.\" And we started arguing."},{"time":1161000,"text":"And people started coming in because they were just outraged."},{"time":1163000,"text":"I had written these crazy things."},{"time":1165000,"text":"And police officers were coming in"},{"time":1167000,"text":"and assistant prosecutors and clerk workers."},{"time":1169000,"text":"And before I knew it, the courtroom was filled with people"},{"time":1171000,"text":"angry that we were talking about race,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"that we were talking about poverty,"},{"time":1175000,"text":"that we were talking about inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"And out of the corner of my eye, I could see this janitor pacing back and forth."},{"time":1180000,"text":"And he kept looking through the window, and he could hear all of this holler."},{"time":1182000,"text":"He kept pacing back and forth."},{"time":1184000,"text":"And finally, this older black man with this very worried look on his face"},{"time":1187000,"text":"came into the courtroom and sat down behind me,"},{"time":1190000,"text":"almost at counsel table."},{"time":1192000,"text":"About 10 minutes later the judge said we would take a break."},{"time":1194000,"text":"And during the break there was a deputy sheriff who was offended"},{"time":1197000,"text":"that the janitor had come into court."},{"time":1199000,"text":"And this deputy jumped up and he ran over to this older black man."},{"time":1201000,"text":"He said, \"Jimmy, what are you doing in this courtroom?\""},{"time":1204000,"text":"And this older black man stood up"},{"time":1206000,"text":"and he looked at that deputy and he looked at me"},{"time":1208000,"text":"and he said, \"I came into this courtroom"},{"time":1211000,"text":"to tell this young man,"},{"time":1213000,"text":"keep your eyes on the prize, hold on.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216000,"text":"I've come to TED"},{"time":1218000,"text":"because I believe that many of you understand"},{"time":1220000,"text":"that the moral arc of the universe is long,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"but it bends toward justice."},{"time":1224000,"text":"That we cannot be full evolved human beings"},{"time":1227000,"text":"until we care about human rights and basic dignity."},{"time":1230000,"text":"That all of our survival"},{"time":1232000,"text":"is tied to the survival of everyone."},{"time":1234000,"text":"That our visions of technology and design"},{"time":1236000,"text":"and entertainment and creativity"},{"time":1238000,"text":"have to be married with visions"},{"time":1240000,"text":"of humanity, compassion and justice."},{"time":1243000,"text":"And more than anything,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"for those of you who share that,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"I've simply come to tell you"},{"time":1249000,"text":"to keep your eyes on the prize, hold on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1251000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1253000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1274000,"text":"Chris Anderson: So you heard and saw"},{"time":1276000,"text":"an obvious desire by this audience, this community,"},{"time":1279000,"text":"to help you on your way and to do something on this issue."},{"time":1282000,"text":"Other than writing a check,"},{"time":1284000,"text":"what could we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1287000,"text":"BS: Well there are opportunities all around us."},{"time":1289000,"text":"If you live in the state of California, for example,"},{"time":1291000,"text":"there's a referendum coming up this spring"},{"time":1293000,"text":"where actually there's going to be an effort"},{"time":1295000,"text":"to redirect some of the money we spend on the politics of punishment."},{"time":1298000,"text":"For example, here in California"},{"time":1300000,"text":"we're going to spend one billion dollars"},{"time":1302000,"text":"on the death penalty in the next five years --"},{"time":1304000,"text":"one billion dollars."},{"time":1307000,"text":"And yet, 46 percent of all homicide cases"},{"time":1309000,"text":"don't result in arrest."},{"time":1311000,"text":"56 percent of all rape cases don't result."},{"time":1313000,"text":"So there's an opportunity to change that."},{"time":1315000,"text":"And this referendum would propose having those dollars"},{"time":1317000,"text":"go to law enforcement and safety."},{"time":1320000,"text":"And I think that opportunity exists all around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1322000,"text":"CA: There's been this huge decline"},{"time":1324000,"text":"in crime in America over the last three decades."},{"time":1327000,"text":"And part of the narrative of that"},{"time":1330000,"text":"is sometimes that it's about increased incarceration rates."},{"time":1333000,"text":"What would you say to someone who believed that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1335000,"text":"BS: Well actually the violent crime rate"},{"time":1337000,"text":"has remained relatively stable."},{"time":1339000,"text":"The great increase in mass incarceration in this country"},{"time":1341000,"text":"wasn't really in violent crime categories."},{"time":1344000,"text":"It was this misguided war on drugs."},{"time":1346000,"text":"That's where the dramatic increases have come"},{"time":1348000,"text":"in our prison population."},{"time":1351000,"text":"And we got carried away with the rhetoric of punishment."},{"time":1354000,"text":"And so we have three strikes laws"},{"time":1356000,"text":"that put people in prison forever"},{"time":1358000,"text":"for stealing a bicycle, for low-level property crimes,"},{"time":1361000,"text":"rather than making them give those resources back"},{"time":1363000,"text":"to the people who they victimized."},{"time":1365000,"text":"I believe we need to do more to help people who are victimized by crime,"},{"time":1367000,"text":"not do less."},{"time":1369000,"text":"And I think our current punishment philosophy"},{"time":1371000,"text":"does nothing for no one."},{"time":1373000,"text":"And I think that's the orientation that we have to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1375000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1377000,"text":"CA: Bryan, you've struck a massive chord here."},{"time":1380000,"text":"You're an inspiring person."},{"time":1382000,"text":"Thank you so much for coming to TED. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1384000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}